Global Flame Retardant Plastic Granule Market Insights
Flame Retardant Plastic Granule Market size was valued at USD 3.5 Billion in 2022 and is projected to reach USD 5.2 Billion by 2030, growing at a CAGR of 6.6% from 2024 to 2030.

Flame Retardant Plastic Granule Market Overview
The global flame retardant plastic granule market was valued at approximately USD 1.23 billion in 2024 and is projected to reach USD 1.78 billion by 2030, growing at a compound annual growth rate (CAGR) of 6.3% during the forecast period. This growth is driven by the increasing demand for fire-resistant materials across various industries, including electronics, automotive, and construction. The market is characterized by the development of halogen-free flame retardant formulations, which are gaining popularity due to environmental and health concerns associated with traditional halogenated flame retardants. Additionally, stringent fire safety regulations are propelling the adoption of flame retardant plastic granules, as industries seek to comply with these standards. The market is also witnessing technological advancements aimed at enhancing the performance and sustainability of flame retardant materials. Key players in the market include RTP, LG Chem, Hanwha Total, Kingfa, Silver, Polyrocks, Julong, Waylam, Keyuan, and Merick Polymers. These companies are focusing on innovation and strategic partnerships to strengthen their market positions.

